public boolean only14(int[] nums) {
  /*
    return false if any element is not (a 1 or a 4)
    else return true
  */
  
  for (int element : nums){
    if (!(element == 1 || element == 4)){
      return false;
    }
  }
  
  return true;
}

/*
Solution from function definition:
  only14 takes an int array and returns true or false
  
Given:
  an int array nums
  
Solution from description with restrictions:
  return true or false
  
Restrictions:
  1. access all element values to test if value is 1 or 4. no need for index
  2. an element is a 1 or a 4
  3. every element passes  test 2 above
  
Intermeditate translations:
  1. for(int value : nums)
  2a. true when (value == 1 || value == 4)
  2b. the converse: false when !(value == 1 || value == 4)
  3.  use the converse to immediately fail the test and return false
  
Solution from description with restrictions and converse:
    return false if any element is not a 1 or a 4
    else return true

Translated solution:
    for each element in array
      if not (element is 1 or element is 4)
        return false
    return true
    
  */
